<@&857649635274915900> If you created your own repo for the project, please don't forget to add a license before the cohort finishes. EPF requires projects to be licensed as Free and Open Source Software. It's really just a minor task of choosing one and adding the license doc to your repo. I noticed some of your repos don't have a license so just a reminder to be aware of that. 
Just reach out if you are not sure or check out licensing tips from FSF https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-recommendations.html https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.html
